parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Lower Control Arm Failure due to Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front lower control arm can cause loss of control, accidents, or strand the driver, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: the front wheel is pitched out at an angle
the vehicle pulls to one side
the tire is no longer pointing in the same direction as the other front tire

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Recall Repair for Front Suspension Control Arm
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the recall repair can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to the failure of the front suspension control arm.
symptoms: as the issue is related to the failure of the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rust and Corrosion in Suspension Components
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rust and corrosion in suspension components can lead to failure of the components, causing loss of control, accidents, or strand the driver.
symptoms: Rust and corrosion observed on suspension components

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket failure can cause coolant and oil leaks, leading to engine overheating, damage, and potential engine failure, which can result in accidents, strand the driver, or cause costly repairs.
symptoms: coolant leaking from the radiator cap or overflow tank
no diagnostic code for engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Wheel bearing failure can cause the vehicle to shake abnormally, leading to loss of control, accidents, or strand the driver.
The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to hesitate, buck, or surge forward, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or bucks at low speeds

or going up a grade or hill; shifting gears takes longer than expected; the tachometer registers high and then erratically jumps down to a much lower level; the vehicle may try to shift while not accelerating; surging forward while changing gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to accelerate forward unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The gear shifter fails to operate as designed; the vehicle accelerates forward while in reverse gear; the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy; the clutch pedal sticks to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle hanger bearing can cause the vehicle to lose control, especially in winter driving conditions, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The rear axle hanger bearing fails; the vehicle's tires are maintained meticulously
but the failure still occurs; symmetrical AWD failure in winter driving is a safety issue.
